HEADWORD: Poon
<hw>Poon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Canarese
<ets>ponne</ets>.]</ety> <def>A name for several East Indian, or their
wood, used for the masts and spars of vessels, as <spn>Calophyllum
angustifolium</spn>, <spn>Calophyllum inophullum</spn>, and
<spn>Sterculia f⟦oe⟧tida</spn>; -- called also
<altname>peon</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poonac</ent>⟦br⟧
